item.title: My First RELEASED Model - Saradomin's Warspear
item.dc:creator: @pluh1 pluh1
item.description:
@pluh1 wrote:

Yeah, uh, same with the other. But after learning that you don’t even know how to color (Which therefore represents that you’re probably a newb at this topic), then I’ll lay a little slack. You have a good shape, just make it more exciting. And also, btw… Sorry to burst your bubble, but it’s sortof pointless as a 2d piece. When you make it 3D, it’ll basically just be a block. It would have been better to either make the shaft rounded on your own, or just use the cylinder primitive to scale it to your likings. Not being harsh, just instructional =) Don’t take anything the wrong way.
